{"author":{"id":"ba392988ea18e62916c24428bd6a4e3b55d4238e1054213c3ef6b3014b2c8cd3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1780650970,"nonce":"lYiHE1LwBIk4tOjW8+QTfgiZ054=","message":"Follow-up: replaced the new timing-sensitive tests with `absurd.fake_now` where the upstream SQL clock controls behavior.\n\nUpdated tests now drive retry, cancellation, and cleanup timing through a single-connection pool plus `set_config('absurd.fake_now', ...)`, staying close to upstream test strategy and avoiding real sleeps for SQL-owned time.\n\nThe only remaining `tokio::time::sleep` in the integration suite is the pre-existing `sleep_until_suspends_then_resumes_from_checkpoint` case. That one is Rust-specific because `TaskContext::sleep_until` compares against Rust `Utc::now()` before scheduling the database resume; `absurd.fake_now` cannot advance that local SDK clock.\n\nValidation after this adjustment:\n\n- `cargo test --all-targets --all-features`\n- `ABSURD_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/absurd_test cargo test-db`\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo fmt --all --check`\n- `git diff --check`","files":null}]}